This product includes software derived from n8n.

The following functions are derived from `ToolsAgent/common.ts` in the package
@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain, published by n8n GmbH under the Sustainable Use
License:

  in nodes/AgentLangfuse/execute.ts

    fixEmptyContentMessage
    getAgentStepsParser
    getOutputParserSchema
    handleAgentFinishOutput
    handleParsedStepOutput
    prepareMessages
    preparePrompt

  in nodes/AgentLangfuse/binaryPassthrough.ts

    extractBinaryMessages
    isImageFile
    isPdfFile
    isTextFile
    processBinaryForAgentPassthrough
    shouldPassthroughBinary

Two deliberate differences remain. This node rejects models that speak the
OpenAI Responses API, so the `input_file` content shape those models require is
not implemented. And the 50 MB ceiling on a binary attachment is n8n's default
rather than its configured `maxAgentPassthroughBinarySizeBytes`, which a
community node cannot read.

